The [[Deranged archaeologist]] is a [[demi-boss]] located on [[Fossil Island]]. A simple mistake during the fight can cause instant death due to his [[special attack]].

He attacks with both [[Ranged]] and [[melee]] but will use only Ranged if the player does not stand in melee distance. Although his [[Magic]] defence stat is quite high, his Magic level is very low, which makes him very easy to hit with Magic. The most effective way to kill the archaeologist is to use Magic from several tiles away while using [[Protect from Missiles]] and avoiding his special attack. '''Note that the archaeologist can use melee attacks on tiles immediately diagonal to him.'''

==Equipment==
The recommended gear setup maximises Magic damage bonus for maximum efficiency.

Prioritise [[Prayer bonus]] over Magic attack bonus, since the archaeologist's low Magic level makes him very easy to hit despite his high Magic defence.

Lower level players or [[ironmen]] seeking [[runite limbs]] can use [[Iban Blast]] for longer but consistent kills.

Recommended skills:
*{{SCP|Magic|50}} for [[Iban's staff]] 
**{{SCP|Magic|75}} for [[Fire Wave]] or [[Powered staff|powered staves]]
*{{SCP|Prayer|40}} for [[Protect from Missiles]]

Recommended inventory:
*2-3 [[Prayer potion]]s ([[Forgotten brew]]s or [[Moonlight moth mix]] can be used to supplement these due to the excess of inventory slots)
*[[Antipoison]] (can drink a dose when banking; is needed only to block poison from the [[spine mushroom]] on the path to the boss)
*[[Digsite pendant]] with Fossil Island teleport option unlocked
*[[Ring of dueling]] to resupply at [[Ferox Enclave]]
*A few pieces of [[food]] (in case you take a hit)
*Runes to cast [[High Alchemy]]
*[[Saturated heart]]
*[[Holy wrench]]
*[[Axe]] for chopping swamp vine
*[[Rake]] for clearing vines, if not using the rubber cap mushroom or magic mushtree to cross the swamp

